title: Rebels DT Robert Nkemdiche out vs. Texas A
text:
Rebels DT Robert Nkemdiche out vs. Texas A&M Daniel Paulling, The Clarion-Ledger 7:01 p.m. CDT October 24, 2015 Ole Miss defensive tackle Robert Nkemdiche is likely to miss Saturday's game against Texas A&M because of a concussion suffered last week against Memphis. (Photo: Justin Ford, Justin Ford-USA TODAY Sports) 1 CONNECT 1 TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
OXFORD — Ole Miss defensive tackle Robert Nkemdiche didn't start Saturday against Texas A&M after suffering a concussion last week against Memphis. 
His injury came in the first half of a 37-24 road upset and forced him to leave the game. The Tigers scored 24 consecutive points from that point and didn’t trail from there. 
Nkemdiche went through concussion protocol throughout this week. Rebels head coach Hugh Freeze said Wednesday evening that Nkemdiche had one portion to pass Thursday morning in order to play against the Aggies. 
Breeland Speaks started in Nkemdiche's place. 
The junior has 17 tackles (5.5 for a loss) and 1.5 sacks on defense and three touchdowns (two rushing, one passing) on offense.
